To alleviate the dispute over the planned transatlantic free trade agreement TTIP, the European Commission has proposed a comprehensive reform of the current arbitration system.
The controversial private arbitration mechanisms for disputes between corporations and states are therefore to be replaced by a more transparent system, which in its operation corresponds to significantly more traditional courts.
"We want to put in place a system that citizens trust," EU Commissioner Cecilia Malmström said at the presentation.
